WHY AGPL: LibreSynergy is software people run as a network service for their
communities. The AGPL's network clause (§13) guarantees that anyone who offers
a modified LibreSynergy over a network must offer that community the modified
source too — so the commons can never be quietly enclosed into a proprietary
product. This is a deliberate, values-driven choice (see MANIFESTO.md). A
community may of course fork and relicense its OWN independent additions as its
own copyright allows.

